The paper deals with the computation of equilibria in resource allocation games, which is a topic that falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also uses combinatorial algorithms and polynomial time algorithms, which are topics that fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC), respectively. The paper also discusses the transformation of a multimarket Cournot competition game to an atomic splittable congestion game, which involves concepts from machine learning (cs.LG) and network economics (cs.NE).
